# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Market Trends — example environment file
# Copy to `.env` (root) or `server/.env` / `web/.env` to override defaults.
# Real `.env` files are git-ignored.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API port (default: 8987)
# PORT=8987

# Market data provider. Options:
#   yahoo — public Yahoo Finance v8 chart API (rate-limited, unofficial)
#   stub  — deterministic synthetic series (good for development & tests)
MARKET_DATA_PROVIDER=stub

# How long (seconds) to cache price responses (default: 3600).
# CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=3600

# Postgres connection string. When unset, the server uses an in-memory
# store (data is lost on restart). Format:
#   postgres://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DBNAME
# For local Postgres.app on macOS, the default socket is at /tmp and the
# `postgres` superuser has no password:
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres@/market_trends?host=/tmp

# ── Web ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Base URL the browser bundle calls for /api. In dev, Vite proxies /api to
# the server (see web/vite.config.ts), so this can stay empty.
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8987
